@Node "Usage" "How to use Inspector."
@{b}
                                   USAGE
@{ub}

Inspector can only be used from the shell, as follows:

   1.> Inspector

There  are  no special arguments to use.  You will need to run Inspector in
combination  with IceBreaker, because you will need to get object addresses
in order to use the View command (more on this later).

If you have KingCON then it is highly recommended that you make use of this
program to view output when using the CLI, as you will have a scroll bar to
view debug history.

Once  you  run  Inspector,  you  will receive a short message and a command
prompt will appear in the CLI.  Type HELP at any time if you get stuck.


                                 @{"Contents" LINK "Main"}
@EndNode
