@Node "Commands" "Inspector command list."
@{b}
                                COMMANDS
@{ub}

Inspector allows you to enter the following commands into the console:

  @{b}View <Address>@{ub}
  Views details on a GMS object that is located at the given address.  If
  you supply an incorrect or unrecognisable address, an error is returned.
  Do not type in addresses of objects that have been initialised and then
  Free()ed, as this will give you an error.

  @{b}HexDump <Address> <Length>@{ub}
  Dumps memory data in neatly formatted hex output.  The memory output will
  start at the given Address, and you may specify the byte length, which is
  optional (the default is to dump 208 bytes of data).

  @{b}TextDump <Address> <Length>@{ub}
  This command is identical to HexDump, but it dumps memory data in text
  format.

  @{b}Help@{ub}
  If you can't remember the commands, type "Help" to get a complete list.

  @{b}Quit@{ub}
  Takes you back to AmigaDOS.

Look out for more commands appearing in future versions!


